d 'BETARK': module for computing Beta regression with autoregressive-corrected errors for proportion outcomes, by joint conditional maximum likelihood.
d
d   betark fits a beta regression model for a continuous proportion
d or rate outcome strictly bounded on (0,1), with autoregressive
d errors of order k in the mean equation's linear predictor. betark
d estimates the mean equation coefficients, the precision (scale)
d equation coefficients, and the AR coefficients rho_1,...,rho_k
d jointly in a single conditional likelihood. This is possible
d because the recursive substitution of Rocha and Cribari-Neto
d (2009) and Ferreira, Figueroa-Zuniga, and de Castro (2015) yields
d a closed-form conditional beta density at each time period, given
d the AR(k) history. 
d
d KW: Beta regression
d KW: autoregressive errors
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260628
d
d Author: Ariel Linden, Linden Consulting Group, LLC
d Support: email alinden@@lindenconsulting.org
d
